<h1>Introduction</h1>

<p>A surprisingly fun and efficient build, the @@@D2HolyFreeze@@@ Zealot is known for his ability to attack large groups of monsters without fear of instant death. Due to the unavoidable slowing effect of @@@D2HolyFreeze@@@, this Zealot is a lot safer than most melee characters and can be built either on a budget or with very high end gear. Definitely recommended to newer players who want to get into playing melee.</p>

<h1>Quick Reference</h1>

<h2>Skill Build</h2>

<p>The following section shows the core skills for the @@@D2HolyFreeze@@@ Zealot. For a detailed breakdown of all core and optional skills as well as the recommended order for allocating skill points, refer to the Skills section of this guide.</p>

<ol>
<li>1 point to all prerequisites</li>
<li>20 points to @@@D2Salvation@@@ - Synergy for @@@D2HolyFreeze@@@, required</li>
<li>20 points to @@@D2ResistCold@@@- Synergy for @@@D2HolyFreeze@@@, required</li>
<li>20 points to @@@D2Sacrifice@@@ - Synergy for @@@D2Zeal@@@, required</li>
<li>20 points to @@@D2Zeal@@@ - Main Damage dealer, invest in @@@D2Sacrifice@@@ first for more Damage or @@@D2Zeal@@@ for more attack rating, required</li>
<li>1+ points to @@@D2HolyShield@@@ - Great for Max Block, required</li>
</ol>

